{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to share with you"},{"time":2000,"text":"some ideas about the secret power of time,"},{"time":4000,"text":"in a very short time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7000,"text":"Video: All right, start the clock please. 30 seconds studio."},{"time":10000,"text":"Keep it quiet please. Settle down."},{"time":15000,"text":"It's about time. End sequence. Take one."},{"time":21000,"text":"15 seconds studio."},{"time":24000,"text":"10, nine, eight, seven,"},{"time":27000,"text":"six, five, four, three, two ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"Philip Zimbardo: Let's tune into the conversation"},{"time":36000,"text":"of the principals in Adam's temptation."},{"time":40000,"text":"\"Come on Adam, don't be so wishy-washy. Take a bite.\" \"I did.\""},{"time":44000,"text":"\"One bite, Adam. Don't abandon Eve.\""},{"time":47000,"text":"\"I don't know, guys."},{"time":50000,"text":"I don't want to get in trouble.\""},{"time":52000,"text":"\"Okay. One bite. What the hell?\""},{"time":57000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"Life is temptation. It's all about yielding, resisting,"},{"time":62000,"text":"yes, no, now, later, impulsive, reflective,"},{"time":65000,"text":"present focus and future focus."},{"time":68000,"text":"Promised virtues fall prey to the passions of the moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"Of teenage girls who pledged sexual abstinence and virginity until marriage --"},{"time":73000,"text":"thank you George Bush --"},{"time":75000,"text":"the majority, 60 percent, yielded to sexual temptations within one year."},{"time":79000,"text":"And most of them did so without using birth control."},{"time":82000,"text":"So much for promises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"Now lets tempt four-year-olds, giving them a treat."},{"time":88000,"text":"They can have one marshmallow now. But if they wait"},{"time":90000,"text":"until the experimenter comes back, they can have two."},{"time":92000,"text":"Of course it pays, if you like marshmallows, to wait."},{"time":95000,"text":"What happens is two-thirds of the kids give in to temptation."},{"time":98000,"text":"They cannot wait. The others, of course, wait."},{"time":101000,"text":"They resist the temptation. They delay the now for later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"Walter Mischel, my colleague at Stanford,"},{"time":107000,"text":"went back 14 years later,"},{"time":109000,"text":"to try to discover what was different about those kids."},{"time":112000,"text":"There were enormous differences between kids who resisted"},{"time":114000,"text":"and kids who yielded, in many ways."},{"time":116000,"text":"The kids who resisted scored 250 points higher on the SAT."},{"time":120000,"text":"That's enormous. That's like a whole set of different IQ points."},{"time":124000,"text":"They didn't get in as much trouble. They were better students."},{"time":127000,"text":"They were self-confident and determined. And the key for me today,"},{"time":129000,"text":"the key for you,"},{"time":131000,"text":"is, they were future-focused rather than present-focused."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"So what is time perspective? That's what I'm going to talk about today."},{"time":137000,"text":"Time perspective is the study of how individuals,"},{"time":140000,"text":"all of us, divide the flow of your human experience"},{"time":143000,"text":"into time zones or time categories."},{"time":145000,"text":"And you do it automatically and non-consciously."},{"time":147000,"text":"They vary between cultures, between nations,"},{"time":149000,"text":"between individuals, between social classes,"},{"time":151000,"text":"between education levels."},{"time":153000,"text":"And the problem is that they can become biased,"},{"time":155000,"text":"because you learn to over-use some of them and under-use the others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"What determines any decision you make?"},{"time":161000,"text":"You make a decision on which you're going to base an action."},{"time":164000,"text":"For some people it's only about what is in the immediate situation,"},{"time":167000,"text":"what other people are doing and what you're feeling."},{"time":170000,"text":"And those people, when they make their decisions in that format --"},{"time":173000,"text":"we're going to call them \"present-oriented,\""},{"time":175000,"text":"because their focus is what is now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"For others, the present is irrelevant."},{"time":179000,"text":"It's always about \"What is this situation like that I've experienced in the past?\""},{"time":182000,"text":"So that their decisions are based on past memories."},{"time":185000,"text":"And we're going to call those people \"past-oriented,\" because they focus on what was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189000,"text":"For others it's not the past, it's not the present,"},{"time":191000,"text":"it's only about the future."},{"time":193000,"text":"Their focus is always about anticipated consequences."},{"time":195000,"text":"Cost-benefit analysis."},{"time":198000,"text":"We're going to call them \"future-oriented.\" Their focus is on what will be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"So, time paradox, I want to argue,"},{"time":203000,"text":"the paradox of time perspective,"},{"time":205000,"text":"is something that influences every decision you make,"},{"time":208000,"text":"you're totally unaware of."},{"time":210000,"text":"Namely, the extent to which you have one of these"},{"time":212000,"text":"biased time perspectives."},{"time":214000,"text":"Well there is actually six of them. There are two ways to be present-oriented."},{"time":217000,"text":"There is two ways to be past-oriented, two ways to be future."},{"time":219000,"text":"You can focus on past-positive, or past-negative."},{"time":223000,"text":"You can be present-hedonistic,"},{"time":225000,"text":"namely you focus on the joys of life, or present-fatalist --"},{"time":228000,"text":"it doesn't matter, your life is controlled."},{"time":230000,"text":"You can be future-oriented, setting goals."},{"time":232000,"text":"Or you can be transcendental future:"},{"time":234000,"text":"namely, life begins after death."},{"time":237000,"text":"Developing the mental flexibility to shift time perspectives fluidly"},{"time":239000,"text":"depending on the demands of the situation,"},{"time":242000,"text":"that's what you've got to learn to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"So, very quickly, what is the optimal time profile?"},{"time":247000,"text":"High on past-positive. Moderately high on future."},{"time":249000,"text":"And moderate on present-hedonism."},{"time":251000,"text":"And always low on past-negative"},{"time":254000,"text":"and present-fatalism."},{"time":256000,"text":"So the optimal temporal mix is what you get from the past --"},{"time":259000,"text":"past-positive gives you roots. You connect your family, identity and your self."},{"time":263000,"text":"What you get from the future is wings"},{"time":265000,"text":"to soar to new destinations, new challenges."},{"time":267000,"text":"What you get from the present hedonism"},{"time":269000,"text":"is the energy, the energy to explore yourself,"},{"time":272000,"text":"places, people, sensuality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"Any time perspective in excess has more negatives than positives."},{"time":280000,"text":"What do futures sacrifice for success?"},{"time":283000,"text":"They sacrifice family time. They sacrifice friend time."},{"time":285000,"text":"They sacrifice fun time. They sacrifice personal indulgence."},{"time":289000,"text":"They sacrifice hobbies. And they sacrifice sleep. So it affects their health."},{"time":294000,"text":"And they live for work, achievement and control."},{"time":297000,"text":"I'm sure that resonates with some of the TEDsters."},{"time":300000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"And it resonated for me. I grew up as a poor kid in the South Bronx ghetto,"},{"time":305000,"text":"a Sicilian family -- everyone lived in the past and present."},{"time":308000,"text":"I'm here as a future-oriented person"},{"time":310000,"text":"who went over the top, who did all these sacrifices"},{"time":312000,"text":"because teachers intervened, and made me future oriented."},{"time":316000,"text":"Told me don't eat that marshmallow,"},{"time":318000,"text":"because if you wait you're going to get two of them,"},{"time":320000,"text":"until I learned to balance out."},{"time":323000,"text":"I've added present-hedonism, I've added a focus on the past-positive,"},{"time":328000,"text":"so, at 76 years old, I am more energetic than ever, more productive,"},{"time":331000,"text":"and I'm happier than I have ever been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"I just want to say that we are applying this to many world problems:"},{"time":336000,"text":"changing the drop-out rates of school kids,"},{"time":338000,"text":"combating addictions, enhancing teen health,"},{"time":341000,"text":"curing vets' PTSD with time metaphors -- getting miracle cures --"},{"time":344000,"text":"promoting sustainability and conservation,"},{"time":346000,"text":"reducing physical rehabilitation where there is a 50-percent drop out rate,"},{"time":350000,"text":"altering appeals to suicidal terrorists,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and modifying family conflicts as time-zone clashes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356000,"text":"So I want to end by saying:"},{"time":358000,"text":"many of life's puzzles can be solved"},{"time":361000,"text":"by understanding your time perspective and that of others."},{"time":364000,"text":"And the idea is so simple, so obvious,"},{"time":366000,"text":"but I think the consequences are really profound."},{"time":368000,"text":"Thank you so much."},{"time":370000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}